def: Acting by the operation of both light and electricity; -- saidof apparatus for producing pictures by electric light.
In a polite or courtly manner; like a gallant or wooer.
A pimple; a small, usually conical, elevation of the cuticle,produced by congestion, accumulated secretion, or hypertrophy oftissue; a papule. Quain.
In a frightful manner; to a frightful dagree.
A flowing through, across, or beyond. [R.]
Letting alone. The let-alone principle, doctrine, or policy.(Polit. Econ.) See Laissez faire.
Pertaining to the city o -- n. sing. & pl.
The act or time of tarrying; delay; lateness. [Archaic] Shak.And after two days' tarriance there, returned. Tennyson.
One more that eleven; two and ten; twice six; a dozen. Twelve-men's morris. See the Note under Morris.-- Twelve Tables. (Rom. Antiq.) See under Table.
